headline: Nvidia, bitcoin and other falling stars drag the US stock market lower
summary: The U.S. stock market sank Monday as Nvidia and other superstars created by the frenzy around artificial-intelligence  technology dimmed some more.  Nvidia was the heaviest weight on the market, as it’s often been in its last couple of tumultuous weeks. The chip company fell 1.8%, while losses for other AI winners included a 6.4% slide for Super Micro Computer.
